      "qwen_observation": "Compilation failed during the Spring Boot 3.3 upgrade step due to Reactor API breaking changes: `doAfterSuccessOrError` was removed in Reactor 3.4+ and `reactor.retry.Retry` was repackaged to `reactor.util.retry.Retry`.",
      "qwen_rationale": "The direct jump from Spring Boot 2.1.6 to 3.3 introduces Reactor 3.5+ which drops several 3.2/3.3 APIs. By inserting an intermediate `UpgradeSpringBoot_2_7` step under JDK 11, we allow OpenRewrite to apply incremental dependency and source transformations in smaller batches. Running 2.7 on JDK 11 avoids JDK 8 classpath conflicts with newer Reactor artifacts, and the subsequent 3.3 step under JDK 17 can then safely apply the remaining jakarta/reactor migrations with a higher chance of successful compilation."
